## Headings
By default, headings have all their font-sizes reset to `1rem`, with the typographic hierarchy enforced by the 'type scale', eg:
<h1 class="u-fs-xl">Heading 1 (u-fs-xl)</h1>
<h2 class="u-fs-l">Heading 2 (u-fs-l)</h2>
<h3 class="u-fs-m">Heading 3 (u-fs-m)</h3>
<h4 class="u-fs-r--b">Heading 4 (u-fs-r--b)</h4>
<h5 class="u-fs-r">Heading 5 (u-fs-r)</h5>
<p class="u-fs-s--b">Small (u-fs-s--b)</p>
<p class="u-fs-s">Small (u-fs-s)</p>

### Breakpoint headings
<p>Font sizes can be triggered at certain breakpoints. Just suffix any font size class with <code>@{breakpoint}</code>, e.g. <code>u-fs-m@l</code></p>
<p class="u-fs-s@xs u-fs-r@s u-fs-m@l u-fs-l@xl u-fs-xl@xxl">This text will change font size depending on viewport width</p>


